HEADWORD: Cantillate
<hw>Can"til*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cantillatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>cantillare</ets> to sing low, dim.
of <ets>cantare</ets>. See <er>Cantata</er>.]</ety> <def>To chant; to
recite with musical tones.</def> <rj><au>M. Stuart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cantillation</ent>⟦br⟧
